column5: Giant freshwater prawns (Udang Galah) are a delicacy in Malaysian seafood cuisine.
Chicken liver (Hati Ayam) is commonly used in curries and stir-fries.
Toasted grated coconut (Kerisik) is used in rendang and coconut-based dishes.
Chicken feet (Kaki Ayam) are commonly used in soups and dim sum.
Beef tenderloin (Daging Batang Pinang) is a premium cut used for rendang and grilling.
Chicken liver (Hati Ayam) is commonly used in curries and stir-fries.
Spanish mackerel (Ikan Tenggiri) is perfect for fish curry and fish paste.
Purple eggplant (Terung Ungu) is commonly used in sambal terung.
Black pepper (Lada Hitam) is a key spice in meat dishes and marinades.
